It makes sense thst humans always push back against the new and strange. Racism, ableism, etc. Have proven that shit. Again and again.

I am what I am, after all. Even when I'm a multi million dollar empire wrenching teeth from humanity to save them from guillotining themselves, I will still be that dumb disabled logger kid. Simultaneous. We are all of our lived experiences.

When your entire lived experience is such a series of various catch 22s, what else can you do but laugh, right? Embrace the superpowers of the disabilities, and forge onwards with a maniacal grin. Use them for positives as much as possible. Embrace the chaos.

One of the trauma responses is isolation, which plays hilariously with Social Anxiety. You never trust anyone - which does awesome for dodging shitheads, but which also tends to isolate you alone for lengthy periods. But that anxiety also allows you to read people like novels.

The shittiest part of being in such a limbo of assured victory with time, is that you are simultaneously present and future, living fractured from both realities. Money is irrelevant, only character, authenticity, integrity, and the like. You test people, gauge their honor, soul.

The biggest part of it all is restraint. Tempered enthusiasm. I know that my plans and goals are assured. But I detest waiting as an ADHD person with no concept of time. So I plan, plot, and wait. Until I can flick my wrist and realize it all when the guillotine finally drops.
